Articles.Content:
I am having so many issues trying to install mods. I don't know if I have too many or what, but I feel like I don't because the youtube videos I have watched have way more mods than I do so I think that it is something I am doing wrong.

 

Currently I have Installed from Curseforge:

 

Drop Tanks (DROP) by Kerbal hacks (1.12.5)

DynoSystem (1.12.5)

FTP Unlimited (1.12.5)

FireSpitter Master (1.11.0)

Kerbal actuators (1.12.2)

 

I don't remember Installing these ones I think they may have been bundled with some other mods:

Infernal Robotics (v3.1.8)

Kerbal Hacks(1.12.5)

Necro Bones (1.4.5)

Repo Soft Tech

Thunder Aero Space (1.12.0)

Module Manger (v4.2.2)

 

I couldn't figure out what game version For Infernal Robotics and I couldn't find any type of version for Repo Soft Tech.

 

Can Someone please tell me what I am doing wrong and how to fix it?
I would suggest installing all mods through CKAN.

41 minutes ago, Scarecrow71 said:

I would suggest installing all mods through CKAN.

So, I tried CKAN but I don't think I did it right. how do I use it and where do I install it?

12 hours ago, lux7328 said:

So, I tried CKAN but I don't think I did it right. how do I use it and where do I install it?

Install CKAN in the same location that you have KSP installed.  You should see a folder for CKAN, as well as the CKAN executable file, inside your KSP folder.  Then launch CKAN from that executable, and you should be good to go.

12 hours ago, lux7328 said:

So, I tried CKAN but I don't think I did it right. how do I use it and where do I install it?

There's a mod installation tutorial that covers manual and CKAN:

And there's a user guide for CKAN itself:

  • https://github.com/KSP-CKAN/CKAN/wiki/User-guide

So, I downloaded CKAN and figured out how to use it, everything is going smoother than before for sure so thanks for that.

However, I am still having one problem I think:

This exception is being thrown and there 2 others that appear to be identical to this one. Any ideas how I can resolve this?

B9Partswitch appears to have been installed with several other mods, I installed it manually into gamedata hoping that would resolve the issue. Do I need to delete all the other B9 Part switches that were installed with other mods and leave the one B9 part switch installed in gamedata?

Is this kind of like when Module manager gets installed with serveral mods and then there are too many?

Edited February 17, 2023 by lux7328

As with all mods, you should only install them using CKAN.  Anything you installed manually is not guaranteed to work.  Personally, I'd suggest uninstalling everything and starting over with just CKAN.
